LAGOS – The Federal Government and technology giants, google, have celebrated the life and time of Samuel Okwaraji, the former Green Eagles player, who slumped and died while playing for Nigeria against Angola at the National Stadium in Surulere, Lagos, on August 12, 1989. The match was a 1990 World Cup qualifier against the Palancas Negras where Nigeria won 1-0, but not without losing one of the country’s best players at that time. Taking to its twitter handle, @FGNigeria, The Federal Government tweeted: “Today, we celebrate one of our past Heroes, Samuel Sochukwuma Okwaraji (19 May 1964 – 12 August 1989), a lawyer turned footballer. He served his father’s land with all might. May the labour of our Heroes never be to celebrate,” the Federal Government tweeted. Meanwhile, Google Doodle, on Sunday, also celebrated the posthumous birthday of Okwaraji. Google Doodle is a special, temporary alteration of the logo on Google’s homepages, intended to commemorate holidays, events, achievements, and notable historical figures. It wrote: “Samuel Sochukwuma Okwaraji was a professional footballer who played internationally for Nigeria. “He was also a qualified lawyer who had a masters degree in international law from the